6 ROS2 - Creating WORKSPACE

  • Open another terminal and run:
mkdir -p ~/ros2_ws/src

cd ~/ros2_ws

git clone https://github.com/ros2/examples src/examples -b humble
  • Build the worksspace:
cd ~/ros2_ws && colcon build --symlink-install

  • In the terminal and run:
colcon test

  • In the same terminal and run:
source install/setup.bash
  • In the same terminal and run:
ros2 run examples_rclcpp_minimal_subscriber subscriber_member_function
  • Open another terminal and run:
cd ~/ros2_ws

 ros2 run examples_rclcpp_minimal_publisher publisher_member_function
  • Open another terminal and run:
sudo gedit  ~/.bashrc
  • add shortcut cmds
echo "alias eb='nano ~/.bashrc'" >> ~/.bashrc
echo "alias sb='source ~/.bashrc'" >> ~/.bashrc
echo "alias gs='git status'" >> ~/.bashrc
echo "alias gp='git pull'" >> ~/.bashrc
echo "alias cw='cd ~/ros2_ws'" >> ~/.bashrc
echo "alias cs='cd ~/ros2_ws/src'" >> ~/.bashrc
echo "alias cb='cd ~/ros2_ws && colcon build --symlink-install'" >> ~/.bashrc
echo "alias sb='source ~/ros2_ws/install/setup.bash'" >> ~/.bashrc
echo "alias sj='source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash'" >> ~/.bashrc

Close the editor, and in the same terminal and run:

source  ~/.bashrc
  • Now you can use short keys:
sb

cw

cs

cb

Reference : https://docs.ros.org/en/humble/Installation.html
